          <p class='first-para'>
            I probably need some advice from my Scottish friends. Actually, this is the third day running that I am happy in principle to say
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_280gc' title='Col. 280GC &mdash; HL Deb 13 September 2004 vol 664 c280GC' name='column_280gc' href='#column_280gc' rel='bookmark'>280GC</a>
            that the noble Lord is exactly right and, if time permits, I should like to come back with a Government adjustment to reflect that situation.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0664P0-06428'>
        <a name='S5LV0664P0_20040913_GCR_102'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-roger-bootle-wilbraham' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040913_GCR_102' title='Link to this speech by Mr Roger Bootle-Wilbraham' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-roger-bootle-wilbraham" title="Mr Roger Bootle-Wilbraham">Lord Skelmersdale</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I am grateful, and I beg leave to withdraw the amendment.
          </p>
