      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0664P0-06621'>
        <a name='S5LV0664P0_20040913_GCR_295'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-terence-higgins' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040913_GCR_295' title='Link to this speech by Mr Terence Higgins' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-terence-higgins" title="Mr Terence Higgins">Lord Higgins</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            As I understand it, I am now speaking to the Question whether Clause 212 shall stand part. The noble Baroness was confused because an earlier version of the grouping presented the clauses in the
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_301gc' title='Col. 301GC &mdash; HL Deb 13 September 2004 vol 664 c301GC' name='column_301gc' href='#column_301gc' rel='bookmark'>301GC</a>
            wrong order. It took me about a quarter of an hour this morning to work out what had happened, and I cannot do it on my feet now.
